messages.message: Hi, just testing our the batches APIs. I mis configured this one, but I got a 200 response, but in the body I got a 404. Should we not return 404 as the response code vs 200 here?

i think for this one because the URL was wrong it didn't even go to any new batch api code, and our generic catch all auth handler is still using the old design (200 and error message). we can improve this -- probably change this for the `api/v2` catch all handler  cc @Anil
I have this on my TODO list already - will fix soon :slightly_smiling_face:
